### Getting Started
After cloning the repo, you'll need to set up the frontend and backend individually.

## Frontend
In the frontend_react folder, run `npm install` to collect all packages.

# Start the frontend development server
In `frontend_react/`, run `npm start` to fire up webpack and start the development server

## Backend
You'll need to `npm install` in the api_express/ folder to sync up the node dependencies.
There are git submodule folders in the api_express/controllers/ folder
    run 'npm submodule update --init <folder'> to get them up to date
the server requires a .env file in the root of api_express/ containing your api keys

# Start backend development server
In `api_express/` run `npm start` to fire up the express erver
    alternatively run 'nodemon start' to enable hot-reloading